Bahrain Bans Any Reporting on Emergency Court Cases, BNA Says

-- B y   V i v i a n   S a l a m a
-- 
2011-04-09T07:20:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-09/bahrain-bans-any-reporting-on-emergency-court-cases-bna-says.html
Bahrain’s government has issued a
ban on any reporting of cases at the National Safety Courts, the
court that handles cases under the emergency law, state-run
 Bahrain News Agency said .  The ban has been issued to “ensure safety of evidences and
guarantee the right of witnesses for legal protection,”
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vivian Salama in  Abu Dhabi  at 
 vsalama@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at  barden@bloomberg.net . 